reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Super easy to build although a few steps were missing on the instruction manual. The item was not what I expected. ( I forgot to check the measurements) It was super small for a nightstand and short. If you have a high bed or like to have a few items on your night stand, this is not the nightstand for you. Other than that it’s great quality and super compact and cute.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: *UPDATE* I just put together the 2nd one I purchased & it's made me think that the 1st 1 was possibly an older version. The sliders for the drawers are different (nicer) than what's on the other night stand & the face of the drawers have a notched space for the handles to sit flush. So the drawers close all the way. My 1 complaint is that estheticly, they aren't exactly the same. The handles aren't the same shape & the color on the handles & legs aren't the same shade. Plus, the face of the drawers is slightly different. By comparison, what I received today is nicer. But I'm not going to worry about it because for the price & considering the amount of time it took to put together, returning 1 just isn't worth it. Besides, I doubt anyone else would even notice. So just be mindful of all this yourselves.*ORIGINAL REVIEW* The box it shipped in was unexpectedly heavy. I've ordered 2 of these, so I assumed they were both in the same box. Surprisingly, it was just the 1 nightstand. There are a bunch of pieces to put together but the instructions were easy to follow & I love that it came with metal Cam Locks. I've bought far more expensive furniture & recieved plastic ones that kept breaking. They even provide you with a little screw driver. Overall, it looks nice & it's sturdy. My only complaint is that the draws overlap a bit, so it doesn't close completely on it's own. But overall, for the price. I'm pleased with my purchase.
